The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) methods for analyzing and quantifying knowledge transfer in neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses explainability and interpretability of ML models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised and supervised learning methods, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions visual exploration, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses pruning of neurons, which is relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
